        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">Ok, passing a pillar is based on the layout of the room (think topdown if it helps).  The room from a topdown angle looks like this:</P><P>XX-----------XX<BR>|             |<BR>|             |<BR>|             |<BR>|             |<BR>XX-----------XX</P><P>With the X's representing the pillars.  What they are refering to is the mobs pathing.  For example if the mob is at the upper right pillar and you are at the lower middle it will come to the right and down to get to you.. but if as it's running you run past the lower left pillar it will turn around and take the long way.</P><P>When you pull the golems if you are in the direct center they will cross through the center and get to you.. but if you are slightly to one side the mob will have to path around the pillars to get to you.</P><P>Sorry I can't explain it better.. but it's easy to get teh hang on once your there.</P><P>-Nandi</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
