		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&id=2097"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
        
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=2097')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&REPLY_ID=67392&TOPIC_ID=3496&FORUM_ID=53&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=Necromancer+Game+Guides&Topic_Title=Howling+Stones+Solo&M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>


        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">I've been soloing in HS from 54 to 57 (made half of my xp in groups tho, in HS or other places). It's pretty easy.</P><P>The spells i use know at 57 are<BR>Vexing<BR>FD<BR>Gate<BR>Root<BR>Dooming<BR>Lich</P><P>The 2 other are asystole + thrall when i break in, the rest of the time they are splurt+ another dot, depending on my mood. I often cast ignite blood, then splurt, then i remove ignite and take asystole. Add vexing and the mob is down.</P><P>The East roamer makes an awesome pet (yes the 51+ skellie). I charm it whenever I can. It's a lot of fun, even if it's rarely very interesting, XP wise... It doesn't resist charm more than any other skel, but it is so tough that you will have a HARD time getting it killed by pyre golems. It can solo 2 golems at a time and still be at 60-70% HP!</P><P>This skel is a killer, if the charm breaks, jump and gate, dont try to recharm (unless you have ST memmed, which could help a lot, but i never do)</P><P>With that pet i was able to clear all 8 golems at 56 sometimes, awesome xp ! But i had to gate most of the time.</P><P>One time i sent it on 2 pyre golems, charm broke, the skel summoned me, i immediately jumped and started to gate, but when it summoned me i aggroed the other side of the door, which resulted in 2 HTs during my fall. Badly sucked to have died in HS, especially with the corpse down there. So, remember it's not really a good idea to send your 51+ pet upstairs ;)</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

